         "id": "e8ec5136-7407-454e-9f2a-515b534b43a5",
         "title": "Serena Kaos: “I decided at 12 that I was going to be very happy. I am happy, but I am not comfortable“",
         "description": "<p><span>Serena Kaos is a Portuguese singer‑songwriter who first caught public attention with a four‑chair turn on “The Voice Portugal” before choosing a harder, quieter route. She moved to London on impulse and began building her career from the street up as an independent busker. With a second album just released, she speaks candidly with Tony Gonçalves about fear, work, and the cost of artistic freedom</span></p>",
